          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Customers Not Cargo Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Transportation (DOT) to revise regulations to:</p> <ul> <li>prohibit an air carrier from forcibly removing a passenger from an aircraft after boarding because the carrier oversold the flight or to provide a passenger seat to an employee of the carrier;</li> <li> establish standards for resolving oversales once an aircraft has been boarded through escalating incentives to passengers to encourage voluntary rebooking; and </li> <li> require an air carrier, to the extent practicable, to resolve issues related to overselling a flight before boarding the flight. </li> </ul> <p> DOT shall consider providing exceptions in such regulations for a medical emergency or a circumstance that poses a threat to the safety of the flight.</p> <ul> </ul>]]></text>
